Data Mining: Web Scraping & Text Analysis of Georgia Tech Faculty
This project demonstrates a complete data mining workflow, starting from raw web data and ending with structured insights, visualizations, and sentiment analysis. It showcases practical skills in web scraping, text preprocessing, NLP, exploratory analysis, and visualization â€” all essential components of modern data science.

Project Overview
The goal of this project is to collect and analyze biography text from faculty members in the Georgia Tech School of International Affairs. The workflow includes:

Scraping faculty profile pages using requests and BeautifulSoup

Extracting names, profile links, and biography text

Cleaning and preprocessing text for NLP tasks

Tokenizing sentences and words

Removing stopwords, punctuation, and noise

Building a termâ€“document frequency matrix

Identifying word associations and common themes

Visualizing results with bar charts and word clouds

Performing sentiment analysis using VADER

This project highlights how unstructured text can be transformed into meaningful insights.

