ðŸ§ª How the Code Works
1. Scraping
Faculty profile URLs are collected from the main directory page, then each profile is visited to extract:

Name

Biography text

Profile link

2. Text Preprocessing
The biography text is cleaned by:

Lowercasing

Removing punctuation

Removing stopwords

Removing numbers

Tokenizing into words and sentences

3. Analysis
The cleaned text is used to compute:

Word frequencies

Most common terms

Word associations

Sentiment scores

4. Visualization
The notebook includes:

Bar charts of top words

Word cloud of top 50 terms

Sentiment line plots

Sentenceâ€‘level sentiment bars

ðŸ“Š Key Insights
Faculty biographies emphasize themes such as international relations, research, policy, global issues, and university engagement.

Sentiment is overwhelmingly neutral or positive, reflecting professional academic tone.

Word associations reveal clusters around research areas and institutional affiliations.

